{"lemma": "عَقَّ", "slug": "عَقَّ", "root": "ع.ق.ق", "root_slug": "ع-ق-ق", "root_link": "/words/roots/ع-ق-ق", "pos": "N", "pos_camel": "noun", "paradigm": [], "frequency_in_corpus": 0, "cross_references": {"qac": {"found": false}, "wiktextract": {"found": true, "entry_count": 1, "pos_tags": ["verb"], "has_etymology": false, "sense_count": 2}, "lanes": {"found": true, "entry_ids": ["n29797"], "search_url": "https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B9%D9%8E%D9%82%D9%8E%D9%91"}}, "translations": {"en": "to slaughter for a child", "fa": "قربانی کردن برای فرزند", "ur": "بچے کے لیے ذبح کرنا", "tr": "çocuğu için kurban kesmek", "id": "menyembelih untuk anak", "bn": "শিশুর জন্য বলিদান করা", "es": "inmolar por el hijo", "fr": "immoler pour l'enfant", "de": "für das Kind schlachten", "ru": "закалывать ради ребенка", "zh": "为子宰牲"}, "definition": {"source": "wiktextract", "senses": [{"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to split, to cleave", "examples": [{"text": "يَعُقُّ الْكُرْدُوسُ بَيْنَ الْمُشَاشَةِ وَجِسْمِ الْعَظْمِ", "english": "The metaphysis separates the epiphysis and the diaphysis."}]}, {"pos": "verb", "gloss": "to be or become disobedient, disrespectful to"}]}, "etymology": null, "ipa": ["/ʕaq.qa/"], "lanes_definition": {"source": "lanes", "entries": [{"entry_id": "n29797", "headword_ar": "عَقَّ", "root": "Eq", "body": [{"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb, K, TA,) aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~N", "text_ar": "عَقٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Mgh, O, Msb, TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He clave, split, slit, ripped,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rent;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, O, Msb, K, TA;) and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he cut."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Mgh, O, TA.) You say,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~a vawobahu", "text_ar": "عَقَّ ثَوْبَهُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He slit, ripped,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rent, his garment."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euq~ato tamiymatuhu fiY baniY fulaAnK", "text_ar": "عُقَّتْ تَمِيمَتُهُ فِى بَنِى فُلَانٍ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "His amulet was cut off among the sons of such a one"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; said of a boy when he has attained to the prime of manhood, and become strong, with a tribe; originating from the fact that as long as the boy was an infant, his mother hung upon him amulets to preserve him from the evil eye; and when he became full-grown, they were cut off from him: whence the saying of a poet,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "bilaAdN bihaA Eaq~a Al$~abaAbu tamiymatiY\n                      \n                     \n                        waA^aw~alu A^aroDK mas~a jilodiY turaAbuhaA"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "A country in which the attaining to the prime of manhood cut off my amulet, and the first land of which the dust touched my skin"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And [hence,]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~ati Alr~iyHu Almuzona", "text_ar": "عَقَّتِ الرِّيحُ المُزْنَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", aor. and inf. n. as above,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The wind drew forth a shower of fine rain from the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mzn", "text_ar": "مزن"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "clouds containing water"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]; as though it rent them. (TA.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euq~ati Als~aHaAbapu", "text_ar": "عُقَّتِ السَّحَابَةُ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The cloud poured forth its water;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[as though it were rent;] and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AinoEaq~at", "text_ar": "اِنْعَقَّت", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[means the same]; (TA;) and ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AEtq~t", "text_ar": "اعتقّت", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[likewise]. (O.) ―         -b3-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~a Eano waladihi", "text_ar": "عَقَّ عَنْ وَلَدِهِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eani Almawoluwdi", "text_ar": "عَنِ المَوْلُودِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (K,) aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, TA) and"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~N", "text_ar": "عَقٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, Msb,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He slaughtered as a sacrifice"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb, K, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for his child,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, Msb,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "for the new-born child,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(K,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "a sheep"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "goat,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, Msb, TA,) ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "generally the latter,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "on the seventh day after the birth."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(T, S, Msb, TA.) And"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He shaved the"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "hair termed"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaqiyqap", "text_ar": "عَقِيقَة"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[q. v.] (S, TA)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of his child,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S,) or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the new-born child."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA.) ―         -b4-  And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~a biAls~ahomi", "text_ar": "عَقَّ بِالسَّهْمِ"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He shot the arrow towards the sky;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and that arrow was called"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EaqiyqapN", "text_ar": "عَقِيقَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (S, O, K;) and it was the arrow of self-excuse: they used to do thus in the Time of Ignorance [on the occasion of a demand for blood-revenge]; and if the arrow returned smeared with blood, they were not content save with the retaliation of slaughter; but if it returned clean, they stroked their beards, and made reconciliation on the condition of the bloodwit; the stroking of the beards being a sign of reconciliation: the arrow, however, as IAar says, did not [ever] return otherwise than clean: (S, O:) the origin was this: a man of the tribe was slain, and the slayer was prosecuted for his blood; whereupon a company of the chief men [of the family of the slayer] collected themselves together to the heirs [who claimed satisfaction for the blood] of the slain, and offered the bloodwit, asking forgiveness for the blood; and if the heir [who claimed satisfaction and who acted for himself and his coheirs] was a strong man, impatient of injury, he refused to take the bloodwit; but if weak, he consulted the people of his tribe, and then said to the petitioners, “ We have, between us and our Creator, a sign denoting command and prohibition: we take an arrow, and set it on a bow, and shoot it towards the sky; and if it return to us smeared with blood, we are forbidden to take the bloodwit, and are not content save with the retaliation of slaughter; but if it return clean, as it went up, we are commanded to take the bloodwit: ” so they made reconciliation; for this arrow never returned otherwise than clean; and thus they had an excuse in the opinion of the ignorant of them. (L, TA.) A poet (S, O, TA) of the family of the slain, said by some to be of Hudheyl, by IB to be El-As'ar El-Joafee, who was absent from this reconciliation, (TA,) says,"}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "Eaq~uwA bisahomK vum~a qaAluwA SaAliHuwA\n                      \n                     \n                        yaA layotaniY fiY Alqawomi A_i*o masaHuwA Alil~uHaY"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "They shot an arrow towards the sky; them they said,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "“ Make ye reconciliation: ”"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "would that I were among the party when they stroked the beards"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: (S, O, TA:) or, as some relate it, the first word is"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~awoA", "text_ar": "عَقَّوْا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", with fet-h to the"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "q", "text_ar": "ق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; which belongs to the class of unsound verbs [i. e. to art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EqY", "text_ar": "عقى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (S, O.) ―         -b5-  One says also,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~a waAlidahu", "text_ar": "عَقَّ وَالِدَهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, K,) or"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^abaAhu", "text_ar": "اَبَاهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (Msb,) aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (S, O, Msb,) inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuquwqN", "text_ar": "عُقُوقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, Msb, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "maEaq~apN", "text_ar": "مَعَقَّةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(S, O, K) and"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~N", "text_ar": "عَقٌّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA,)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He was undutiful, disobedient, refractory,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ill-mannered, to his parent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "father; contr. of"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "bar~ahu", "text_ar": "بَرَّهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "; (K;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he broke his compact of obedience to his parent,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "father;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(TA;)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he disobeyed his father;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "failed,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "neglected, to behave to him in a good,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "comely, manner."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Msb.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~a Alr~aHima", "text_ar": "عَقَّ الرَّحِمَ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", (TA, and Ham p. 93,) like"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "qaTaEahaA", "text_ar": "قَطَعَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[i. e."}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He severed the tie,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "ties, of relationship, by unkind behaviour to his kindred"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]. (Ham ib.) And"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~a", "text_ar": "عَقَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[alone], aor."}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "EuquwqN", "text_ar": "عُقُوقٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "He was undutiful,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he acted undutifully,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.; or]"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "he contravened,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "or"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "opposed, him whom he was under an obligation to obey."}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(Har p. 158.)"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euquwqu", "text_ar": "عُقُوقُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlwaAlidayoni", "text_ar": "الوَالِدَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Undutiful treatment,"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "&c.,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "of the two parents"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] is said in a trad. to be one of the great sins. (O.) And it is said in a prov.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEuquwqu", "text_ar": "العُقُوقُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "A^aHadu Alv~ukolayoni", "text_ar": "اَحَدُ الثُّكْلَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Undutiful treatment of a parent is one of the two sorts of being bereft of a child"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: or, as some relate it,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlEuquwqu vukolu mano lamo yavokalo", "text_ar": "العُقُوقُ ثُكْلُ مَنْ لَمْ يَثْكَلْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "Undutiful treatment of a parent is"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(like)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "the bereavement of him who is not"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(really)"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "bereft of his child"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "]: i. e. he whom his children have treated undutifully ("}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mino Eaq~ahu waladuhu", "text_ar": "مِنْ عَقَّهُ وَلَدُهُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ") is as though he were bereft of his children although they are living. (O.) [See also 3: and 4.] ―         -b6-  Hence, from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Euquwqu", "text_ar": "عُقُوقُ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlwaAlidayoni", "text_ar": "الوَالِدَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the verb is metaphorically used in the saying, in a trad.,"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "mavalukumo wamavalu EaAy^i$apa mavalu AlEayoni", "text_ar": "مَثَلُكُمْ وَمَثَلُ عَايِشَةَ مَثَلُ العَيْنِ"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "fiY Alr~aA^osi tuw^o*iY SaAHibahaA walaA yasotaTiyEu A^ano yaEuq~ahaA A_il~aA", "text_ar": "فِى الرَّاْسِ تُوْذِى صَاحِبَهَا وَلَا يَسْتَطِيعُ اَنْ يَعُقَّهَا اـِلَّا"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "biA@l~a*iY huwa xayorN lahaA", "text_ar": "بِا@لَّذِى هُوَ خَيْرٌ لَهَا"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "(tropical:)  ["}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The similitude of you and of 'Áïsheh is that of the eye in the head, when it hurts its owner, and he cannot treat it severely save with that which is good for it:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "app. meaning that her severity was for the good of the objects thereof]. (TA.)       -A2-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~a", "text_ar": "عَقَّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", intrans., said of lightning: see 7.       -A3-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~ato", "text_ar": "عَقَّتْ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "said of a mare, and of an ass: see 4.       -A4-"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~ati Ald~alowu", "text_ar": "عَقَّتِ الدَّلْوُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", inf. n."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~u", "text_ar": "عَقُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", means"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "The bucket came up full from the well;"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and some of the Arabs say"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~at", "text_ar": "عَقَّت"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "as having"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taEoqiyapN", "text_ar": "تَعْقِيَةٌ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "for its inf. n.; but it is [said to be] originally ↓"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eaq~aqat", "text_ar": "عَقَّقَت", "orth_type": "arrow"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", the third"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "q", "text_ar": "ق"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "being changed into"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Y", "text_ar": "ى"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ", [which is then in this case suppressed,] like as they said"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "taZan~ayotu", "text_ar": "تَظَنَّيْتُ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "from"}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "AlZ~an~u", "text_ar": "الظَّنُّ"}, {"kind": "text", "text": ": [it is, however, mentioned in the TA in art."}, {"kind": "arabic", "text_bw": "Eqw", "text_ar": "عقو"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "also, and there expl. as meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it rose"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in the well"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "turning round:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "and from what here follows, it appears to mean"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "it rose swiftly, cleaving the air:"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "] a poet, cited by IAar, says, of a bucket,"}, {"kind": "page_break", "n": 2096}, {"kind": "quote", "text": "Eaq~ato kamaA Eaq~ato daluwfu AlEiqobaAnN"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "meaning"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "It clave"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "[the air of] the well,"}, {"kind": "italic_en", "text": "rising swiftly, like the hastening of the swift eagle"}, {"kind": "text", "text": "in its flight towards the prey. (TA in the present art.)"}], "source_refs": ["Msb", "K", "TA", "Mgh", "O", "S", "T"]}]}, "classical_definitions": null, "translations_attribution": {"model": "qwen36-35b-heretic", "generated_date": "2026-05-18", "pipeline_version": "words.translation.v1.spark"}}